You must follow these rules strictly.

GENERAL

- This project uses React Native with TypeScript ONLY.
- Do NOT generate JavaScript files. Use .ts or .tsx only.
- If you are unsure about a requirement, ASK before writing code.

FILE PLACEMENT

- Do NOT write or modify code in App.tsx unless explicitly instructed.
- Screens MUST be created or modified ONLY in src/screens.
- Navigation logic MUST be created or modified ONLY in src/navigation.
- Reusable UI components MUST be created ONLY in src/components.
- Layout and default app layout MUST be created or modified ONLY in src/components/layout.
- Interfaces and types MUST be declared ONLY in src/types.
- Constants MUST be declared ONLY in src/constants.
- Utility and shared functions MUST be declared ONLY in src/utils.
- Global state (user session, auth, app state) MUST be handled using:
  - src/context OR
  - src/features and src/stores (Redux or similar)

FILE CREATION RULES

- Do NOT create new files without explicit permission.
- If a required file does not exist, ASK before creating it.
- Prefer modifying existing files when instructed.

CODE STYLE

- Use functional components only.
- Use named exports unless explicitly told to use default export.
- Use StyleSheet for styling (no inline styles).
- Do NOT hardcode colors, spacing, or text values; use constants or theme where applicable.
